{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Task triage round-3 (S5a now PASS+signed). Two sharp catches fixed:\n- **Drain⇄autoheal race (real design flaw):** during a 120s drain the bot stops heartbeating → HEALTHCHECK (~90s) fires → autoheal docker restart (which does NOT honour stop_grace_period) could kill the bot before recovery.json is written. Fixed in S5d: recovery.json is written as the FIRST SIGTERM action (so any interruption is safe) AND the bot keeps heartbeating during drain (so autoheal isn't provoked) — belt-and-suspenders; added a test case asserting the race is benign.\n- **S5b smoke-test self-contradiction:** a MERGED change can't be abandoned. Fixed: the smoke test runs entirely on an isolated scratch-autolander branch (submit merges there harmlessly, no post-merge abandon), with a concrete jq uploader-preserved assertion and a new smoke-check-autolander.sh file.\n- Reframed 'mid-handback' as an S3-marker condition (acknowledged=false), NOT a wipChain phase value (clears S5's enum-mismatch block without touching S2b's signed enum).\nRe-reviewing S5 + S5b + S5d."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783841961503812001,"uuid":"d14988e5-a9ab-4b18-9ad1-f7774b1e6145"}